# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Firebase config for the Quarterly Knowledge Check pilot.
#
# 1. Create a Firebase project at https://console.firebase.google.com
# 2. Add a Web App to the project (the </> icon) — no hosting needed.
# 3. Enable Firestore Database (Build → Firestore Database → Create, start in
#    test mode for the pilot, or use the rules in firestore.rules).
# 4. Copy the config values from Project Settings → Your apps → SDK setup.
# 5. Save this file as `.env.local` (NOT committed — it is gitignored) and fill
#    in the values below.
# 6. Restart `npm run dev` so Vite picks up the new env vars.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

VITE_FIREBASE_API_KEY=
VITE_FIREBASE_AUTH_DOMAIN=
VITE_FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_STORAGE_BUCKET=
VITE_FIREBASE_MESSAGING_SENDER_ID=
VITE_FIREBASE_APP_ID=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Firebase Admin (server-side identity + protected Firestore projections).
#
# Preferred: set the complete downloaded service-account JSON as one env value
# (compact/quoted on one line in `.env.local`; Railway can store the JSON value
# directly). Never prefix it with VITE_ or commit it. Split vars are an alternative.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
FIREBASE_SERVICE_ACCOUNT_JSON=
# FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=
# FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=
# FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY=

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Gemini scenario generation (server-side ONLY — used by /api/generate-scenarios).
#
# These are NOT VITE_-prefixed on purpose: Vite never bundles them into the
# browser, so the key stays private. On Vercel, set them as Environment Variables
# in the project settings. For local `vercel dev`, put them in `.env.local`.
#
# - GEMINI_API_KEYS: one or more free Google AI Studio keys
#   (https://aistudio.google.com/apikey), comma-separated. The function rotates to
#   the next key whenever one is rate-limited, maximising the free-tier budget.
#   (A single GEMINI_API_KEY is also accepted as a fallback.)
# - GEMINI_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS: optional per-upstream-call abort timeout. Defaults
#   to 25000 and is clamped to 1000–120000.
# - CALL_QA_GRADER_MODEL: the SINGLE pinned model used to score the Call QA Test.
#   Scored Call QA grading must be auditable and calibrated against ONE model — it
#   rotates across API keys but never falls back to a different (lower-quality)
#   model. Defaults to the calibrated primary model (gemini-2.5-flash) when unset;
#   an empty/whitespace value falls back to the same default. Only override this to
#   deliberately re-pin the grader after re-calibration. (Advisory practice grading
#   and other non-scored endpoints keep their normal model-fallback behavior.)
# - CALL_QA_DRAIN_TIMEOUT_MS: optional bound (default 8000) on the server-side
#   Call QA End-Call transcript-drain handshake. After the navigator ends the call,
#   the relay signals end-of-audio upstream and waits at most this long for a final
#   transcription boundary before finalizing. A drain that times out finalizes the
#   attempt as capture_incomplete (graded, but flagged for mandatory supervisor
#   review) — it is never silently treated as a clean capture.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
GEMINI_API_KEYS=
GEMINI_REQUEST_TIMEOUT_MS=25000
# CALL_QA_GRADER_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash
# CALL_QA_DRAIN_TIMEOUT_MS=8000

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Supervisor session (server-side authorization).
#
# Supervisor-only authoring endpoints (/api/generate-scenarios, /api/refine-sop)
# now require a signed, HttpOnly session cookie issued by /api/supervisor-login.
# All values below are SERVER-ONLY (never VITE_-prefixed, never bundled).
#
# - SUPERVISOR_PASSCODE_SERVER: the passcode /api/supervisor-login validates.
#   REQUIRED on Railway/Vercel/production. Deployed processes fail closed when
#   it is absent; the bundled demo value is local/test convenience only.
# - SESSION_SIGNING_SECRET: HMAC key for signing session tokens. Set a long random
#   value in production. If unset, a passcode-derived key is used (pilot fallback).
# - ALLOW_LEGACY_API_SECRET: set to `true` to also accept the old body.secret
#   value on protected endpoints (staged rollout / local tooling). Off by default.
# - ALLOW_LEGACY_API_SECRET / GENERATION_SECRET: emergency staged-rollout
#   compatibility only. Leave unset; normal requests use Firebase ID tokens.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
SUPERVISOR_PASSCODE_SERVER=
SESSION_SIGNING_SECRET=
ALLOW_LEGACY_API_SECRET=
GENERATION_SECRET=

# SAFE ROLLOUT ORDER:
# 1. Add all VITE_FIREBASE_*, Firebase Admin, supervisor, and Gemini variables.
# 2. Deploy the identity-enabled server and verify navigator + supervisor login.
# 3. Publish firestore.rules. Publishing the rules before step 2 locks clients out.
